# fmu-v3 hil_ppp NuttX defconfig
#
# Extends the nsh base config with:
#   - IPv4 / TCP / UDP network stack
#   - TUN virtual interface (required by netutils/pppd)
#   - ALLOW_BSD_COMPONENTS (required for NET_TUN)
#   - netutils/pppd + netutils/chat
#   - USART3 (TELEM2, /dev/ttyS2) reconfigured for 115200 baud PPP,
#     large DMA buffers, NO hardware flow control (pppd uses nocrtscts)
#   - USART2 (TELEM1, /dev/ttyS1) at 115200 default; rc.board_ppp reconfigures
#     to 921600 at runtime for direct QGC / companion connections (-r 80000)
#
# All other settings are inherited from boards/px4/fmu-v3/nuttx-config/nsh/defconfig
# via the NuttX merge mechanism (px4_impl_os.cmake falls back to nsh/ for any
# key not present here, but defconfig files are complete snapshots so we carry
# the full nsh content below and add the delta at the end).
#
# DO NOT hand-edit the base section; use "make menuconfig" then
# "make px4_fmu-v3_hil_ppp savedefconfig" to regenerate.
#

